lege basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |mode              = Basketball\n  |year              = 1981\u201382\n  |prev_year         = 1980\u201381\n  |next_year         = 1982\u201383\n  |team              = St. Francis Terriers\n  |image             = StFrancisBrooklynTerrierswordmark.png\n  |conference        = ECAC Metro\n  |division          = North Division\n  |short_conf        = \n  |CoachRank         =\n  |APRank            =\n  |record            = 10\u201317  \n  |conf_record       = 8\u20137\n  |head_coach        = [[Gene Roberti]]\n  |hc_year           = 3rd\n  |asst_coach1       = \n  |ac1_year          =\n  |asst_coach3       =\n  |ac3_year          =\n  |stadium           = [[Generoso Pope Athletic Complex]]\n  |champion          =\n  |bowl              =\n  |bowl_result       =\n}}\n{{1981\u201382 ECAC Metro men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''1981\u201382 St. Francis Terriers men's basketball team''' represented [[St. Francis College]] during the [[1981\u201382 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The team was coached by [[Gene Roberti]], who was in his third year at the helm of the St. Francis Terriers. The Terriers played their homes games at the  [[Generoso Pope Athletic Complex]]. This is the teams first year in the newly organized ECAC Metro Conference, which will later be known as the [[Northeast Conference]]. Also at this time the conference had 2 divisions, north and south, with St. Francis competing in the north division.\n\nThe Terriers finished their season at 10\u201317 overall and 8\u20137 in conference play. They participated in the [[1982 ECAC Metro Men's Basketball Tournament]] and lost in the opening round to Long Island 53\u201356.\n\n==Roster==\n\n{{CBB roster/Header |hdr_txtcolor=white|subhdr_txtcolor=white|hdr_bgcolor=#0038A8|subhdr_bgcolor=#CE1126|year=1981|team=St. Francis Brooklyn Terriers|sex=men|high_school=yes}}\n\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Ken       |last=Berry      |num=  |pos=G  |ft=5|in=11|lbs=   